 -- Eugenio Paolantonio (g7) <me@medesimo.eu>  Thu, 05 Sep 2013 23:05:01 +0200

linstaller (5.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fixed full removal of features introduced in 2a95e429b15a7d760e8dda9a5a09778ced89c14d.
    For some strange reason, python-apt won't find the package in cache, even if the changes are still not commited.
    This commit workarounds that, but the issue should be inspected in detail.
  * libmodules/partdisks: lvm: added methods VolumeGroup.enable(), VolumeGroup.disable() and enable_all_vgs().
    enable_all_vgs() are now called after every lvm refresh to ensure that there aren't any disabled volumegroups.
  * debian/gbp.conf: restored master-worthy configuration.
  * Upload to current.

 -- Eugenio Paolantonio (g7) <me@medesimo.eu>  Thu, 05 Sep 2013 15:03:58 +0200

linstaller (4.99.6-1) devel; urgency=low

  * partdisks: use path instead of mapper_path on LUKS devices to do checking and locking.
    This may be slower, but now linstaller can lock and properly check mountpoints on
    an encrypted partition unlocked by foreign applications.
  * partdisks: warn the user if LUKSdrive.close() failed.
  * bricks: inst: ensure we remove every dependencies of the features' meta-packages.
  * userhost: inst: set groups if root is disabled.

 -- Eugenio Paolantonio (g7) <me@medesimo.eu>  Thu, 29 Aug 2013 17:26:11 +0200

linstaller (4.99.5-1) devel; urgency=low

  * Mount virtual partitions via new module virtualpartitions.inst, AFTER unsquash.
    This avoids overwriting on some virtual /dev devices such as /dev/shm.
    Also *FINALLY* fixed that stupid revert bug in partdisks.inst. I'm a moron.
  * debian/linstaller-modules-base.install: ship virtualpartitions.inst.

