 -- Eugenio Paolantonio (g7) <me@medesimo.eu>  Thu, 01 Aug 2013 13:07:37 +0200

linstaller (4.71.0-1) devel; urgency=low

  * Ensure we properly prepare the /boot/efi partition
  * Support for markup in header's subtext, which is now properly resizes too long texts
    modules/bricks: frontend/glade: changed subtext.
  * Ensure we try to umount boot/efi in the wrappers.
  * frontends/glade: added support for fullscreen (set frontends:glade.fullscreen to True)
    config/: added semplice-fullscreen config which uses the newly implemented fullscreen function
  * Ensure the apply window is sensitive before showing it
  * Improved resize actions, some bugfixes
  * Added LVM Logical Volume modification support, along with resizing.
    In a LV, rely on pyparted only to get the fileSystem.
    If a LV exists but has a None filesystem, assume it's fat32.
    Migration to standard kilobytes (SI).
  * Disable 'Use for LVM' box if we are in a LV
  * Move newtable and delete buttons to the new 'advanced options'
  * Preliminary VG manage GUI
  * Latest GRUB fucked up the (hd0) method, get the first drive by ourselves...
  * More progress on the VGmanage window.

 -- Eugenio Paolantonio (g7) <me@medesimo.eu>  Mon, 22 Jul 2013 20:25:55 +0200

linstaller (4.70.1-1) devel; urgency=low

  * Improvements, workarounds, fixes on the APT handling inside and outside the chroot.
    Cache() now (mostly) works in both situations, unlike the upstream apt.cache.Cache().
    And that's so fuckin' great.
    Also, grub-efi installation now works correctly.

 -- Eugenio Paolantonio (g7) <me@medesimo.eu>  Thu, 27 Jun 2013 19:12:41 +0200

linstaller (4.70.0-1) devel; urgency=low

  * Added settings support for frontends.
  * Added new setting -p|--configpath to select the path where search for linstaller configurations
  * config/thewall-test: added test thewall config.
  * frontends/cli: added "follow" setting.
  * Added supermodules support (a virtual module which calls a set of modules defined on the configuration file).
  * Added some simple test modules.
  * Added support for user-defined target directory (-t switch).
  * Added seed_setup() function in module.py, override this to set-up things before seeding occours.
  * Check for modu before revert.
  * modules/partdisks: library: mount_partition added support for mount type.
  * modules/timezone: front/glade: ensure we focus the timezone treeview.
  * Added the basics of LVM and Crypting support.
    Nothing works yet (as it is still not finished ;D) and the current GUI may be changed at any time.
    Still, tracking it in GIT seems the best thing to do to avoid huge commits later.
    I hope to get it finished soon!
  * lvm.py: do not use python-lvm for now. Added LogicalVolume and and VolumeGroup classes.
    The lvm library now does something useful.
  * modules/partdisks: added base LVM view and modify (edit view and format) support.
  * partdisks can now add a new LV.
  * partdisks: properly set do_not_format_box if we should not format.
  * partdisks can now delete LVs.
  * partdisks can now clear entire VGs.
  * Do not fail if LVM devices have some I/O errors and can't be used
  * Ensure we idle_add the refresh action after we applied things
  * Added a nice APT library along with the supportrepo module (set-ups the support repo present in latest snapshots)
  * modules/bootloader: inst: fetch bootloader from supportrepo, if we can
  * core/main: support for enums.
  * debian/control:
    - linstaller: depend on python-apt
    - linstaller-modules-base: remove dependency on grub (or firmware-raspberrypi), bootloaders are now in iso
    - Changed URL of the project
  * debian/linstaller-modules-base.install: ship supportrepo

 -- Eugenio Paolantonio (g7) <me@medesimo.eu>  Tue, 25 Jun 2013 11:43:18 +0200

