  * debian/control: fixed dependencies in the linstaller-modules-echo package.

 -- Eugenio Paolantonio (g7) <me@medesimo.eu>  Sat, 10 Mar 2012 20:38:46 +0100

linstaller (2.13.1-1) pulse; urgency=low

  * config/semplice-persistent-nolive: removed isolinux seed.
  * setup.py: ship echo.
  * debian/: new package linstaller-modules-echo; ship semplice-persistent configs.

 -- Eugenio Paolantonio (g7) <me@medesimo.eu>  Sat, 10 Mar 2012 19:25:05 +0100

linstaller (2.13.0-2) pulse; urgency=low

  * config/: added semplice-persistent and semplice-persistent-nolive configurations. 
  * linstaller.py: handle submodules as well.
  * partdisks: library: added return_partition, setFlag, unsetFlag functions.
  * modules/echo: preleminary release of echo.
  * config/semplice-persistent: partdisks: disable swap, enable skip_to_selection and onlyusb.
  * partdisks: added onlyusb and skip_to_selection seeds; do not tell the use that we're are
               formatting partitions if root_noformat is True (as we are not formatting root,
               which is the partition that user don't want to be wiped).
  * modules/echo: added fake module where store shared things.
  * linstaller.py: remove last word after last dot only if it's "inst" or "front".
  * modules/echo/partusb: use a pythonic-way to create the empty file.
  * modules/partdisks: added ability to not mount virtual (/proc, /dev, /sys) partitions.
  * modules/summary: do not crash if something is missing, usb-persistence support.
  * modules/echo/partusb: added frontend.
  * config/semplice-persistent: some changes.

 -- Eugenio Paolantonio (g7) <me@medesimo.eu>  Sat, 10 Mar 2012 18:56:03 +0100

